Date: 0/0/1987
Source: Boards, Blades & Barebellies
Author: OGONOWSKA-COATES
Vol / Page: 98
Edition:
Quote: <i>Wool shed.</i> Building in which sheep are shorn. Inside it is divided into pens where the unshorn sheep are held and which take up most of the room; the board on which the shearers work; the wool room at the top or side of the board where the wool is classed, pressed and stored. Some woolsheds have a loft built up over the pens for extra wool storage.
Notes:

